[3]
Date: Thu 25 Oct 2007
Source: Daily Echo, Dorset [edited]
<http://www.thisisdorset.net/display.var.1787425.0.animal_movements_restricted_in_county.php>


Farmers in Dorset are being made subject to new government control
zones that restrict animal movements. Defra has extended the
Bluetongue Control Zone from Kent and East Sussex into East Dorset.

The rules follow a new case of the disease in Sevenoaks, and means
farmers of cattle, sheep, goats, and deer may not move them outside
the designated zone apart from to slaughter.

Vehicles used to transport animals to slaughterhouses must also be
sprayed with approved insecticidal spray prior to loading. The
movement controls do not apply to pigs.

Defra has written to all recorded owners of animals within the
affected districts advising them of this change and urging vigilance.

--
